## Bundled third-party software

This project orchestrates external scientific tools delivered as Docker images.
Those tools carry their own licenses, which apply independently of this MIT
grant:

- **Rosetta** (`rosettacommons/rosetta`): non-commercial / academic license.
  Commercial use requires a separate license from the University of Washington.
  See https://www.rosettacommons.org/software/license-and-download
- **RFdiffusion** (`rosettacommons/rfdiffusion`): BSD-3-Clause.
- **PyMOL Open-Source** (`pegi3s/pymol`): see container labels; the open-source
  PyMOL is BSD-style. Schrödinger's commercial PyMOL is not used.
- **ColabFold / AlphaFold**: see upstream — Apache-2.0 for ColabFold; AlphaFold
  weights are CC-BY 4.0 with non-commercial use restrictions in some cases.

The MIT license here covers the chaperonin orchestrator code only. You are
responsible for complying with the upstream tools' licenses when you deploy
them via chaperonin.
